Always read PROJECT_CONTEXT.md before writing any code.
Follow the DynamoDB key schema exactly as defined in PROJECT_CONTEXT.md — no deviations.
Never use scan() on DynamoDB. Never use FilterExpression as a substitute for proper key design.
This is a demo app — keep code simple and functional, not production-grade.
Backend: Node.js 22.x Lambda functions. AWS SDK v3 only (@aws-sdk). 
Use CommonJS (require/module.exports) for Lambda handlers.
CDK: Runtime.NODEJS_22_X
Infrastructure: AWS CDK JavaScript only. One stack: UniConsultationsStack.
Bedrock: use converse() API, model amazon.nova-lite-v1:0, region eu-west-1.
Frontend: React + Vite, no TypeScript, no Tailwind, no component libraries. Plain CSS modules.
When writing Lambda handlers: always handle OPTIONS method and return CORS headers.
Do not add features not listed in PROJECT_CONTEXT.md.